channel.title: What is your love language?
channel.description:
Alright, this is something I'm kind of curious about. I've noticed there have been a lot of relationship troubles within this forum ranging from not knowing how to handle a specific situation with a girlfriend, all the way down to causing women to hide and flee when you enter the room.
This page: [url]https://www.5lovelanguages.com/profile/singles/[/url]
is a questionnaire that will help you pin point the ways you yourself feel appreciated, and it will also help you be aware of all the ways other people show and feel affection.
I'm curious to know what everyone is going to get. I'm going to guess that physical contact is going to score very highly here. I scored a 12 in quality time, and a 9 in physical contact, but I took this test a while ago before I was engaged in a relationship, and physical contact was at 11 or something, because I was feeling starved for it I guess.
Anyways, just answer the questions honestly and post your scores/discuss anything related.
I got 12 quality time 9 physical contact and the others were all very low, I don't remember the exact numbers because it was a little while ago that I did it. :stuck_out_tongue: Words of affirmation was the next in order, I know that.

item.title: What is your love language?
item.dc:creator: FERGUS
item.description:
So I guess I don’t like gifts. Doesn’t suprise me, I’ve never really understood the reason for giving people gifts at christmas, birthdays or whatever other reasons there are. I can’t remember if I ever appreciated a gift in the last 10 years.

I appreciate time spent together and people caring for me, nothing new here. Words don’t mean jackshit to me, the only reason it even have score here is because I found the alternatives lacking and picked the closest one.

To be honest this didn’t teach me anything new, I’ve spent so much time thinking through the years.
If you don’t know who you are yourself, how are you supposed to learn to know someone else?

3 Words of Affirmation
10 Quality Time
0 Receiving Gifts
10 Acts of Service
7 Physical Touch
